<div id="review_2787842874" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2787842874" />
    <a title="Britany" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5550397-britany"><img alt="Britany" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533999441p2/5550397.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2787842874?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Britany" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Britany" href="/user/show/5550397-britany">Britany</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5550397-britany?shelf=2019">2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2787842874" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8758377222915358959">Thea Kronberg is the girl we all wish we could be. <br/><br/>She dreams of a bigger world, of traveling, and befriending all the interesting people she crosses. She develops her musical gift by first starting to play the piano and then continuing to sing. She crosses teachers and develops her craft. This novel follows Thea throughout her life, taking the reader along for the ride.<br/><br/>In the beginning, the ride was interesting and thrilling and dreamy. In the middle, it slowed down and started getting bogged d</span>
  <span id="freeText8758377222915358959" style="display:none">Thea Kronberg is the girl we all wish we could be. <br /><br />She dreams of a bigger world, of traveling, and befriending all the interesting people she crosses. She develops her musical gift by first starting to play the piano and then continuing to sing. She crosses teachers and develops her craft. This novel follows Thea throughout her life, taking the reader along for the ride.<br /><br />In the beginning, the ride was interesting and thrilling and dreamy. In the middle, it slowed down and started getting bogged down in tedious details. The end helped bring this story full circle, but I was ready for this story to end when I reached the final page. Thea starts so bright and full of life, and ends up talented, but is this everything she thought it would be? Is she truly happy to put everything else to the side? Living a life devoted to her craft and music. <br /><br />I really enjoyed parts of this and there were other sections that were utterly droll and boring. I'm landing right down the middle and may need to think more on this one. I think it's one that needs to settle in for awhile.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8758377222915358959" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
