        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer105469416" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6479162869852173605"><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17150.My__ntonia' title='My Ántonia by Willa Cather' rel='nofollow noopener'>My Antonia</a> is one of my favorite books, so I thought I&apos;d revisit Willa Cather since it&apos;s been a long time. While I found myself savoring little morsels of prose here and there, overall this novel was too long, and frankly, I just didn&apos;t care that much about the main character. I think I would have enjoyed this book more if 200 pages had been edited out so that the story was tighter and there weren&apos;t so many descriptive passages that really weren&apos;t relevant in the long run.<br/><br/>Of course, in those ver</span>
  <span id="freeText6479162869852173605" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17150.My__ntonia" title="My Ántonia by Willa Cather" rel="nofollow noopener">My Antonia</a> is one of my favorite books, so I thought I'd revisit Willa Cather since it's been a long time. While I found myself savoring little morsels of prose here and there, overall this novel was too long, and frankly, I just didn't care that much about the main character. I think I would have enjoyed this book more if 200 pages had been edited out so that the story was tighter and there weren't so many descriptive passages that really weren't relevant in the long run.<br /><br />Of course, in those very details that I would chop, Cather is painting (beautifully, as always) realistic and detailed pictures of Scandanavian immigrant families. I guess you can't have it all. But if you want to read Cather at her best, I'd try <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17150.My__ntonia" title="My Ántonia by Willa Cather" rel="nofollow noopener">My Antonia</a> or <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/140963.O_Pioneers___Great_Plains_Trilogy___1_" title="O Pioneers! (Great Plains Trilogy, #1) by Willa Cather" rel="nofollow noopener">O Pioneers!</a> instead.</span>
